[
A^akomatu *
] ― -b2- xayolN kumotN, and kamaAtiY~N↓, (K,) and kamaAtaY, of the same measure as Ea*aAraY, (TA,) Horses of the colour of that which is called kumayotN, (K,) kmt is a pl. formed from A^akomatu; though this sing. has not been used: (L:) and kmAtY is a pl. formed from kamotaA'u [fem. of A^akomatu] regarded as a subst.; though this sing. also has not been used. (TA.)
